{"title_page": "1992 Esiliiga", "text_new": "{{Infobox football league season\n  | competition        = [[Esiliiga]]\n  | season             = 1992\n  | winners            = [[Kreenholm Narva]]\n  | promoted           = \u2013\n  | relegated          = \u2013\n  | continentalcup1    = \n  | continentalcup1 qualifiers = \n  | continentalcup2    = \n  | continentalcup2 qualifiers = \n  | continentalcup3    = \n  | continentalcup3 qualifiers = \n  | league topscorer   = \n  | total goals        = \n  | average goals      = \n  | biggest home win   = \n  | biggest away win   = \n  | highest attendance = \n  | lowest attendance  = \n  | average attendance = \n  | prevseason         = <!-- Other name? -->\n  | nextseason         = [[1992\u201393 Esiliiga|1992\u201393]]\n}}\nThe '''[[1992 in football (soccer)|1992 season]]''' in the first division of [[Estonia]]n football, named '''[[Esiliiga]]''', was the first domestic competition since the [[Baltic states|Baltic nation]] gained [[independence]] from the [[Soviet Union]] in 1991. Eight teams competed in this edition, played in the spring, with [[Kreenholm Narva]] winning the title.\n\n==Final Round I==\n{{#invoke:sports table|main|style=WDL\n|res_col_header=Q\n|winpoints=2\n\n|team1=KRE|name_KRE=[[Kreenholm Narva]]\n|team2=TEM|name_TEM=Tempo Tallinn\n|team3=LOK|name_LOK=Lokomotiiv Valga\n|team4=MET|name_MET=Metallist Tallinn\n|win_KRE=3|draw_KRE=1|loss_KRE=2|gf_KRE=13|ga_KRE=9\n|win_TEM=3|draw_TEM=0|loss_TEM=3|gf_TEM=16|ga_TEM=14\n|win_LOK=2|draw_LOK=1|loss_LOK=3|gf_LOK=11|ga_LOK=17\n|win_MET=2|draw_MET=0|loss_MET=4|gf_MET=13|ga_MET=15\n\n|col_C=green1|text_C=\n|result1=C\n|update=complete|source=\n}}\n\n==Final Round II==\n{{#invoke:sports table|main|style=WDL\n|res_col_header=Q\n|winpoints=2\n|highest_pos=5\n\n|team5=PKK|name_PKK=Peipsi Kalur Kallaste\n|team6=P\u00c4R|name_P\u00c4R=KEK P\u00e4rnu\n|team7=LOK|name_LOK=Lokomotiiv Valga\n|team8=PAI|name_PAI=KEK Paide\n|win_PKK=3|draw_PKK=1|loss_PKK=2|gf_PKK=13|ga_PKK=10\n