{"title_page": "Circuito de Baloncesto de la Costa del Pac\u00edfico", "text_new": "{{Infobox Sports league\n| title           = Circuito de Baloncesto de la Costa del Pac\u00edfico\n| current_season  = 2020 CIBACOPA season\n| logo            = cibacopa.jpg\n| pixels          = 200px\n| sport           = Basketball\n| founded = {{start date and age|2001||}}\n| inaugural       = \n| teams           = [[#Current clubs|10]]\n| country = [[Mexico]] \n| champion        = [[Rayos de Hermosillo]]<br/> (3rd title)\n| most_champs     = [[Rayos de Hermosillo]]<br>[[Tijuana Zonkeys]]<br>[[Trigueros de Ciudad Obreg\u00f3n]]<br>(3 titles each)\n| website         = [http://www.cibacopa.org www.CIBACOPA.org]\n| continent = [[FIBA Americas]] ([[Americas]]) \n| director = Antonio G\u00e1ndara Gonz\u00e1lez\n| TV              =  AYM Sports<br>FIBA Am\u00e9ricas TV<br>iTV Deportes<br>Latin American Sports<br>[[Megacable|Mega Sports]]<br>[[Telemax (television network)|Telemax]]<br>Televisoras Grupo Pac\u00edfico<br>[[TVC Deportes]]<ref>includes [[TVC Deportes 2]]</ref>\n| related_comps   = \n| founder         = \n| footnotes       = \n}}\nThe '''Circuito de Baloncesto de la Costa del Pac\u00edfico''' ('''CIBACOPA''') is a basketball league based in Northwestern Mexico. As of 2018, it involves 10 clubs, primarily from northwest Mexico.<ref>{{cite news|last=Motley|first=Gene|title=Former Chowan hoops player retires in style|url=https://www.roanoke-chowannewsherald.com/2018/07/26/former-chowan-hoops-player-retires-in-style/|work=The Roanoke-Chowan News Herald|date=26 July 2018|accessdate=20 August 2018}}</ref> The matches take place from March to June.\n\nThere have been speculations of a further league expansion with the beginning of the 2019 season.<ref>{{cite news|last=Gonz\u00e1lez|first=\u00c1ngel|title=Expansi\u00f3n en Cibacopa |url=https://www.frontera.info/Columnas/DetalleColumnas/1020082-Apuntes-Angel-Gonzalez.html|work=FRONTER.INFO|date=26 September 2018|accessdate=20 October 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Teams ==\n<section begin=map />\n{{location map+ |Mexico |float=left |width=500 |caption=Locations of the CIBACOPA teams |places=\n{{location map~ |Mexico |lat=32.525 |long=-117.033333|label=<div style=\"font-size:80%;\">[[Tijuana Zonkeys|Zonkeys]]</div> |position=bottom}}\n{{location map~ |Mexico |lat=27.918333 |long=-110.898889 |label=<div style=\"font-size:80%;\">[[Ostioneros de Guaymas (basketball)|Ostioneros]]</div>|position=top}}\n{{location map~ |Mexico |lat=25.783497 |long= -108.993742 |label=<div style=\"font-size:80%;\">[[Pioneros de Los Mochis|Pioneros]]</div> |position=top}}\n{{location map~ |Mexico |lat=24.80485 |long= -107.385497 |label=<div style=\"font-size:80%;\">[[Caballeros de Culiac\u00e1n|Caballeros]]</div>|position=bottom}}\n{{location map~ |Mexico |lat=23.22    |long=-106.42 |label=<div style=\"font-size:80%;\">[[Venados de Mazatl\u00e1n (basketball)|Venados]]</div>|position=right}}\n{{location map~ |Mexico |lat=24.142222 |long=-110.310833 |label=<div style=\"font-size:80%;\">[[Mantarrayas de La Paz|Mantarrayas]]</div> |position=left}}\n{{location map~ |Mexico |lat=27.489167 |long=-109.935 |label=<div style=\"font-size:80%;\">[[Halcones de Ciudad Obreg\u00f3n|Halcones]]</div> |position=bottom}}\n{{location map~ |Mexico |lat=29.098889 |long= -110.954167 |label=<div style=\"font-size:80%;\">[[Rayos de Hermosillo|Rayos]]</div> |position=top}}\n{{location map~ |Mexico |lat=20.666667 |long=-103.35 |label=<div style=\"font-size:80%;\">[[Gigantes de Jalisco|Gigantes]]</div> |position=bottom}}\n}}<section end=map />\n\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"width:100%\"\n|-\n|-\n!Team\n!City\n!Arena\n!Capacity\n!Member Since\n!Head coach\n|-  \n|'''[[Caballeros de Culiac\u00e1n]]'''\n|[[Culiac\u00e1n]], [[Sinaloa]]\n|[[Parque Revoluci\u00f3n]]\n|align=\"center\" |2,000\n| align=\"center\" | 2000\n|{{flagicon|Mexico}} Andr\u00e9s Contreras\n|-  \n|'''[[Gallos de Aguascalientes (basketball|Gallos de Aguascalientes]]''' \n|[[Aguascalien