 Usul Perkembangannya] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303171319/http://fastion.multiply.com/journal/item/9/MAKALAH_TAFSIR |date=3 March 2016 }}</ref>\n* Tafsir al-Nur by Prof. T. M. Hasbi Ash-Shiddiqi in 1956.<ref name=\"fastion.multiply.com\"/><ref>[http://hasunmax.blogspot.com/2010/02/tafsir-nur.html Tafsir an-Nur] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304063726/http://hasunmax.blogspot.com/2010/02/tafsir-nur.html |date=4 March 2016 }}</ref>\n* Tafsir al-Azhar by [[Hamka]].<ref>[http://mtamim.wordpress.com/2008/02/29/download-e-book-tafsir-al-azhar-hamka/ Tafsir al-Azhar] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160306180938/http://mtamim.wordpress.com/2008/02/29/download-e-book-tafsir-al-azhar-hamka/ |date=6 March 2016 }}</ref>\n* [[Tafsir Al-Mishbah]] by [[Quraish Shihab]].<ref>[http://www.lentera-hati.com/crn/TafsirAl-Mishbah.shtml Tafsir al-Mishbah] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090310082034/http://www.lentera-hati.com/crn/TafsirAl-Mishbah.shtml |date=10 March 2009 }}</ref>\n\n===Italian===\n* Ventura, Alberto, Milano, 2010. p. LXXII+900 (traduzione di Ida Zilio-Grandi).\n*[[Hamza Roberto Piccardo|Piccardo, Hamza Roberto]], 1994: Saggio di Traduzione Interpretativa del Santo Corano inimitabile.\n* Bausani, Alessandro, Firenze 1955, p.lxxix+779, Firenze 1978, p. lxxix+771.\n* Bonelli, Luigi, new ed. Milano 1929, p.&nbsp;31+524, reprint 2nd rev. ed., Milano: Ulrico Hoepli 1972, p.&nbsp;614. (4)\n* Branchi, Eugenio Camillo, Roma 1913, p.&nbsp;437.\n* Calza, Caval. Vincenzo, Bastia 1847, p. xiv+330.<ref>[[:s:it:Corano|Read on Wikisource in Italian language]]</ref>\n* Aquilio, Milano 1914, p.lxx+[6]+340+359.\n* Moreno, Martino Mario, Torino 1967, p. viii+605, Torino 1969, p. viii+605\\ 2nd ed. [n.p.] 1971, p. vii+608.\n* Violante, Alfredo, Rome: Casa Ed. Latina 1912.\n* Il Corano, Milano 1882/ Milano 1913.<ref>[http://www.quran.org.uk/articles/ieb_quran_translators.htm The Qur'an and its Translators Il Corano] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120621190007/http://www.quran.org.uk/articles/ieb_quran_translators.htm |date=21 June 2012 }}</ref>\n* ''L'Alcorano di Macometto: nel qual si contiene la dottrina, la vita, i costumi, et le leggi sue / tradotto nuovamente dall' Arabo in lingua Italiana.'', 1547, Venise.\n\n===Japanese===\nThere are at least seven complete translations of Qur'an:\n* Sakamoto, Ken-ichi, 1920, ''K\u014dran Ky\u014d'' (\u30b3\u30fc\u30e9\u30f3\u7d93), in ''Sekai Seiten Zensh\u016b'' 14\u201315 (Sacred Writings of the World), Tokyo: Sekai Seiten Zensh\u016b Kankoukai. (translated from Rodwell's English version)\n* Takahashi, Goro, et al. 1938, ''Sei K\u014dran Ky\u014d'' (\u8056\u9999\u862d\u7d93), Tokyo: Sei K\u014dran Ky\u014d Kankoukai.\n* [[Sh\u016bmei \u014ckawa|Okawa, Shumei]], 1950, ''K\u014dran'' (\u53e4\u862d), Tokyo: Iwasaki Shoten.\n* [[Toshihiko Izutsu|Izutsu, Toshihiko]], 1957, rev. 1964, ''K\u014dran'' (\u30b3\u30fc\u30e9\u30f3), 3 vol. Tokyo: [[Iwanami Shoten, Publishers|Iwanami Shoten]]. (translated from Arabic)\n* Fujimoto, Katsuji, et al. 1970, ''K\u014dran'' (\u30b3\u30fc\u30e9\u30f3), in ''Sekai no Meicho'' 15 (Masterpieces of the World), Tokyo: [[Chuokoron-Shinsha]]. (republished in 2002, in ''Ch\u016bk\u014d Classics'' E6-7, 2 vol.)\n* Mita, Ryoichi, 1972, ''Sei Kur\u0101n'' (\u8056\u30af\u30e9\u30fc\u30f3), Tokyo: Japan Muslim Association; 2nd. ed. 1983, ''Sei Kuru\u0101n'' (\u8056\u30af\u30eb\u30a2\u30fc\u30f3) (bilingual in Arabic and Japanese)\n* Holy Quran with Japanese translation. Islam International Publications Limited.<ref>[http://www.alislam.org/quran/tafseer/?page=-8&region=JP Japanese translation] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161226082745/http://www.alislam.org/quran/tafseer/?page=-8&region=JP |date=26 December 2016 }}</ref>\n\n===[[Javanese language|Javanese]]===\n* Maulana Muhammad Ali, ''Qur'an Suci Jarwa Jawi'', Darul Kutubil Islamiyah, Jakarta, Indonesia, 2001.\n\n===[[Kannada language|Kannada]]===\nThere are at least three complete translations of Qur'an:\n* Divya Qur'an, Qur'an Majid, (An effort of six scholars: Mawlana Shah Abd al-Qadir, Mawlana Sayyid, Abu Raihan [[Ahmed Noori]], Abd Allah Sahib, I'jaz al-Din and [[Shaikh Abdul Gaffar Sullia]]), 2 vol. Bangalore 1978, p.&nbsp;1400.\n* Pavitra Qur'an by [[Shaikh Abdul Gaffar Sullia]].(online version available<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.kannadaquran.com |title=Archived copy |accessdate=12 November 2010 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161021064843/http://kannadaquran.com/ |archivedate=21 October 2016 }}</ref>)\n* Qur'an Vyakhyana by [[Shaikh Abdul Gaffar Sullia]]\n* Kannada Meaning of Holy Qur'an, Part 30 (Juz 'Amma) by Iqbal Soofi. (online version<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.kanquran.blogspot.com |title=Archived copy |accessdate=22 January 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161203232906/http://kanquran.blogspot.com/ |archivedate=3 December 2016 }}</ref> and <ref>{{cite web |url=https://kannadaquran.wordpress.com/%E0%B2%AA%E0%B2%B5%E0%B2%BF%E0%B2%A4%E0%B3%8D%E0%B2%B0-%E0%B2%95%E0%B3%81%E0%B2%B0%E0%B3%8D%E2%80%8D%E0%B2%86%E0%B2%A8%E0%B3%8D-30-%E0%B2%A8%E0%B3%86%E0%B2%AF-%E0%B2%AD%E0%B2%BE%E0%B2%97/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=7 December 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304142320/https://kannadaquran.wordpress.com/%E0%B2%AA%E0%B2%B5%E0%B2%BF%E0%B2%A4%E0%B3%8D%E0%B2%B0-%E0%B2%95%E0%B3%81%E0%B2%B0%E0%B3%8D%E2%80%8D%E0%B2%86%E0%B2%A8%E0%B3%8D-30-%E0%B2%A8%E0%B3%86%E0%B2%AF-%E0%B2%AD%E0%B2%BE%E0%B2%97/ |archivedate=4 March 2016 }}</ref>)\n* Sarala Quran: Surah Al Fatihah, Al-Baqarah, Ali Imran, An-Nisaa, Al-Maaidah, Al-An'aam and Al-Aaraf by Iqbal Soofi.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://kn.wikipedia.org/s/1z0p|script-title=kn:\u0cb8\u0cb0\u0cb3 \u0c95\u0cc1\u0cb0\u0ccd\u200c\u0c86\u0ca8\u0ccd|trans-title=Simple Qur'an|work=[[Kannada Wikipedia]]}}</ref> The web version also contains translation of all the 37 Surahs of last/30th part of Qur'an. Translation of Al-Baqarah, Ali Imran An-Nisaa, Al-Maaidah and Al-An'aam is also published to the web. (ongoing project, online edition<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.saralaquran.blogspot.com |title=Sarala Quran |accessdate=1 October 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160316120923/https://kannadaquran.wordpress.com/ |archivedate=16 March 2016 }}</ref>)\n* Holy Qur'an is a free Kannada Quran applet for Android smartphones / tablets.  The original Arab pages are derived from <nowiki>http://tanzil.net</nowiki> and translated into Kannada transliteration by Muhammed Hamza Puttur, Umar Ibn Ahmed Madini, Ahmad SM and Abu Bakr Nazir Salafi reviewed 'PAVETHRA QURAN' Complete Kannada Meaning' (publisher: Salafi Publishing House Mangalore ).\n* \"Pavithra Quran\" Kannada translation quran: all quran (translator and publisher  South karnataka salafi movement \u00ae ( SKSM) Mangalore 2016)<ref>[https://www.facebook.com/public/Sksm-Mangalore ]{{dead link|date=December 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\n*Pavithra Qur'an  - Translated by Muhammad Yusuf Sahib of Mangalore. Edited by M.P. Ibrahim Sahib of Manjeshwer.\n\n===Kashmiri===\n* Kashmiri translation published in Saudi Arabia\n* A translation in Kashmiri is also available by Mirwaiz Mohammad Yousuf Shah.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.maktabah.org/quran/translations/798-the-noble-quran-with-translation-in-kashmiri-language-saudi-edition.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=18 April 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121125130301/http://maktabah.org/quran/translations/798-the-noble-quran-with-translation-in-kashmiri-language-saudi-edition.html |archivedate=25 November 2012  }}</ref>\n\n===[[Kazakh language|Kazakh]]===\n* by [[Musa Bigiev]], 1912, unpublished\n* by Aq\u0131t Ulimjiul\u0131, lost\n* by [[Sadwaqas Ghylmani]], 1970s\n* by \u011eazez Aq\u0131tul\u0131 & Maqa\u015f Aq\u0131tul\u0131, 1990, 