 to... |accessdate=18 January 2007 |last=York |first=Malachi |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071008013425/http://www.destee.com/forums/archive/index.php/t-36212.html |archive-date=8 October 2007 |url-status=dead  }}</ref>\n\n===Macedonian===\n* Hasan D\u017eilo, 1997, ''\u041a\u0443\u0440\u02bc\u0430\u043d \u0441\u043e \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0432\u043e\u0434'' (\"the Qur\u02bcan with a Translation\"), [[King Fahd Complex for the Printing of the Holy Quran]] ([[Medina]], [[Saudi Arabia]]).\n* Elena Tren\u010devska\u2013\u010cekovi\u1e31, Mersiha Smailovi\u1e31, Jasmin Red\u017eepi, 2011, ''\u041f\u0440\u0435\u0432\u043e\u0434 \u043d\u0430 \u0437\u043d\u0430\u0447\u0435\u045a\u0435\u0442\u043e \u043d\u0430 \u0411\u043b\u0430\u0433\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0434\u043d\u0438\u043e\u0442 \u041a\u0443\u0440\u0430\u043d'' (\"Translation of the meaning of the Noble Qur\u02bcan\"), ArtBooks ([[Skopje]], [[North Macedonia]]) ({{ISBN|978-9989-190-49-0}}).\n\n===Madura===\n* Translation by Jamaah Pengajian Surabaya (JPS) led by K.H. Sattar.<ref>[http://nu.or.id/page/id/dinamic_detil/1/16433/Warta/Tashih_Al_Qur_an_Madura_Molor.html Tashih Al-Qur'an Madura Molor] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160308102808/http://nu.or.id/page/id/dinamic_detil/1/16433/Warta/Tashih_Al_Qur_an_Madura_Molor.html |date=8 March 2016 }}</ref>\n\n===[[Malayalam]]===\n* Cheriyamundam Abdul Hameed Madani and Kunhi Mohammed Parappoor with online links.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://hameedmadani.hudainfo.com |title=Archived copy |accessdate=17 April 2010 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161008145934/http://hameedmadani.hudainfo.com/ |archivedate=8 October 2016 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hudainfo.com/Translation.asp |title=Archived copy |accessdate=26 January 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150405214405/http://hudainfo.com/Translation.asp |archivedate=5 April 2015  }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.malayalamquransearch.com |title=Archived copy |accessdate=4 April 2011 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160502180658/http://www.malayalamquransearch.com/ |archivedate=2 May 2016 }}</ref>\n* 'Albayan Fee Ma\u2019anil Quran' by Sayyid Ahmed Shihabuddeen Imbichikkoya Thangal, former Chief Qazi of Kozhikode.<ref name=\"malayalamquransearch.com\">{{cite web |url=http://www.malayalamquransearch.com/docs/?p%3D6 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=24 April 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150428083811/http://www.malayalamquransearch.com/docs/?p=6 |archivedate=28 April 2015 }}</ref>\n* 'Fathahu-rahman Fee Thafseeril Quran\u2019 by KV Muhammed Musliyar Koottanad, former Joint Secretary of [[Samastha Kerala Jamiyyathul Ulama]]<ref name=\"malayalamquransearch.com\"/>\n* ''Tafheem ul Quran'' by Abul A\u00e1la Maudoodi with online links.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://thafheem.net/Sura_Index.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=21 August 2011 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161207203010/http://thafheem.net/Sura_Index.html |archivedate=7 December 2016 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.abulala.com |title=Archived copy |accessdate=21 October 2008 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160402143717/http://www.abulala.com/ |archivedate=2 April 2016 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.jihkerala.org/htm/malayalam/Quran_Bashyam/Quran_Bashyam.htm |title=Archived copy |accessdate=22 September 2008 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100830135530/http://www.jihkerala.org/htm/malayalam/Quran_Bashyam/Quran_Bashyam.htm |archivedate=30 August 2010  }}</ref>\n* Quran Lalitha Saram Translation By Sheik Muhammed Karakunnu and Vanidas Elayavur.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.lalithasaram.net |title=Archived copy |accessdate=20 January 2010 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161023224348/http://www.lalithasaram.net/ |archivedate=23 October 2016 }}</ref>\n* Quran Bodhanam By TK Ubaid.\n* Translation by Muttanisseri Koyakutty Maulavi.\n* Translation by K. Abdul Rahiman and P.A. Karim and K.A. Raoof (D.C. Books).\n* Translation by Adonne Publishing Group, Thiruvananthapuram.\n* Translation by Current Books Kottayam.\n* Translation  by [[Rahmathullah Qasimi]]\n* Translated by Muhammad Abul Wafa Sahib (Marhoom) of Kozhikode. Edited by Moulvi Muhammad Ismail Saheb of Aleppey and some distinguished Quran Scholars.\n\n===Maldivian===\n* Quran Tharujamaa by Shaikh Abu Bakr Ibrahim Ali. This is the first translation in [[Maldivian language]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://islamicfoundationofthemaldives.org |title=Archived copy |accessdate=20 May 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304001649/http://islamicfoundationofthemaldives.org/ |archivedate=4 March 2016  }}\"</ref>\n\n===[[Mandar language|Mandar]]===\n* Translation by Muh. Idham Kholid Budi in 2005<ref>{{cite web |url=http://alquran-batak.blogspot.de/2009/11/terjemahan-al-quran-ke-dalam-bahasa.html |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20120630231717/http://alquran-batak.blogspot.de/2009/11/terjemahan-al-quran-ke-dalam-bahasa.html |url-status=dead |title=Blog nicht gefunden. |date=30 June 2012 |archivedate=30 June 2012 |website=archive.is}}</ref> available online.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rappang.com/2010/02/alquran-bahasa-mandar-indonesia.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=27 May 2011 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160319162537/http://www.rappang.com//2010/02/alquran-bahasa-mandar-indonesia.html |archivedate=19 March 2016 }}</ref>\n\n===[[Mande languages|Mande]]===\n* [[Souleymane Kante]]\n* Moulana Abul A'la Moudoodhi{{Citation needed|date=August 2013}}\n\n===Manipuri===\n* The Holy Quran, Arabic text with Manipuri translation. Translated into Manipuri from English translation by Ahmad Hasan (Manipuri) under the auspices of [[Mirza Tahir Ahmad]].<ref>[http://www.alislam.org/quran/tafseer/?page=-10&region=MP MAnipuri translation] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161226091439/http://www.alislam.org/quran/tafseer/?page=-10&region=MP |date=26 December 2016 }}</ref> ({{ISBN|978-1-85372-436-7}}).\n\n===Norwegian===\n* Einar Berg, [[Universitetsforlaget]], 1980. ({{ISBN|82-00-05371-7}}).\n\n===Pashto===\nThere are numerous translations of the [[Qur'an]] in [[Pashto language|Pashto]]. Some of the most famous are listed below:\n* Mawlana Muhammad Ilyas (Akhunzada): The most first translation of Quran as well as ''Fakhr-ut-Tafseer'' was written by him in the 18th century in Afghanistan (original versions are placed in [[Kandahar]]), He then came to Peshawar (warsak road mathra kochian) & wrote many more Islamic books as well as search prescription of different kind of diseases, he was a Mowlana as well as a complete doctor & chemist.\n* ''Fakhr-ut-Tafaaseer' and ''Mukhzin-ut-Tafeer'' by Mawlana Muhammad Ilyas Akhunzada Peshawari Kochiani is considered one of the famous Tafseers of the Quran in Pashto.\n* Muhammad Fathullah Khan Kandahari's translation: Printed in the 18th century, [[Bhopal]], India, Translates the Quran in [[Pashto language|Pashto]]. It was translated from Shah Abdul Qadar Dehlavi's Urdu translation of the Quran. The hand-written versions of this translation are saved in Raza library of Rampur and Idara-e-Adabyat-e-Urdu library of Deccan, Hyderabad, India.\n* ''[[Mulavi Murad Ali Khan Sahibzada|Tafseer Yaseer]]'' by Mulavi Murad Ali Khan Sahibzada, it was the first Tafseer and second translation in the Pashto language. The first volume of this Tafseer was completed in 1912 and the second in 1917 It was the most famous Tafseer of its time. Murad Ali Sahebzada was born in 1223 H.q. He studied the traditional subjects of that time like Sarf, Nahwa, Hekmat, Fiqh & Meerath, Tafseer, Hadith, Uruz and Literature and he was also the Hafiz of the Quran. He was a good writer, author, teacher, and Poet of his time. His son Mohammad Sahebzada writes about him \"He has written unlimited number of poems in Pashto, Dari, Arabic and Hindi. Writing poem was such easy for him, that he won't feel any difference between poem and prose. He has written a lot of Ghazals on Monotheism and Wisdom. His handwriting was very good and quick.\" <Akser Al Qoloub></Mohammad Sahibzadah.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.answers.com/topic/mulavi-murad-ali-khan-sahibzada#ixzz3TFisLHFH |title=Answers - The Most Trusted Place for Answering Life's Questions |website=Answers.com}}</ref>\n* Mawlana Abdullah and Mawlana Abdul Aziz: It is a translation of the Tafseer of Mawlana Abdul Haq Darbangawi and Mawlana Wa'iz Kashifi. Translated by Mawlana Abdullah and Mawlana Abdul Aziz, it was printed in 1930 in Mumbai, India.\n* Dr. Din Muhammad Khan: It is a word by word translation of the Quran printed in early years.\n* Mawlana Janbaz Sarfaraz Khan: It is printed in early years and is considered of the famous translation.\n* ''Aziz-ut-Tafaaseer'' by Mulavi Sultan Aziz Khan.\n* Mulavi Farooq Khan Ghalzi: It is a Pashto translation of the Quran printed in early years.{{Citation needed|date=August 2013}}\n\n===Persian===\nThere are more than 60 complete translations of Qur'an in Persian and many partial translations. In the past some [[Tafsir]]s which had included Qur'an were translated like translation of [[Tafsir al-Tabari]] in 10 CE.<ref>[http://www.al-shia.com/html/far/books/quran&olum/quran_paju/q_pagh04.htm \u0642\u0631\u0622\u0646 \u0648 \u0642\u0631\u0622\u0646 \u067e\u0698\u0648\u0647\u0649<!-- Bot generated title -->]  {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110830093923/http://www.al-shia.com/html/far/books/quran%26olum/quran_paju/q_pagh04.htm |date=30 August 2011 }}</ref>\n\n* [[Salman the Persian]] (7th century) (partial translation)\n* ''Qur'an Quds'', translator unknown \u2013 (before the 10th century)\n* A translation in 556 AH\n* Saiyad Makhdoom Ashraf Jahangir Simnani (1308\u20131405 CE) Original Manuscript at Mukhtar Ashraf Library in Kichoucha Shareef (U.P.)\n* Shah Waliullah (1703\u20131762)\n* Mahdi Elahi-Ghomshei, (\u0645\u0647\u062f\u06cc \u0627\u0644\u0647\u06cc\u200c\u0642\u0645\u0634\u0647\u200c\u0627\u06cc).\n* Mahdi Fouladvand (\u0645\u0647\u062f\u06cc \u0641\u0648\u0644\u0627\u062f\u0648\u0646\u062f) available online.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hawzah.net/Per/Q/QA/Quran.htm |title=Archived copy |accessdate=16 March 2007 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140223090019/http://www.hawzah.net/per/Q/QA/Quran.htm |archivedate=23 February 2014 }}</ref>\n* [[Naser Makarem Shirazi]] (\u0646\u0627\u0635\u0631 \u0645\u0643\u0627\u0631\u0645\u200c\u0634\u064a\u0631\u0627\u0632\u06cc), translation includes his inline tafsir within parenthesis.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.andisheqom.com/page.php?pg%3Dquran%26sor%3D1 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=16 March 2007 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070502021701/http://www.andisheqom.com/page.php?pg=quran |archivedate=2 May 2007  }}</ref>\n* Malik Fahd Council, [[Sunni]] branch.\n* Ghodratollah Bakhtiarinejad (\u0642\u062f\u0631\u062a \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647 \u0628\u062e\u062a\u064a\u0627\u0631\u06cc \u0646\u0698\u0627\u062f) available online.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.quran-farsi.net |title=Archived copy |accessdate=16 March 2007 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141205075516/http://www.quran-farsi.net/ |archivedate=5 December 2014 }}</ref>\n* [[Tahere Saffarzadeh]], translated Qur'an in Persian and English (Bilingual) in 2001.\n\n===Polish===\n* Jan Murza Tarak Buczacki.\n* [[J\u00f3zef Bielawski (arabist)|J\u00f3zef Bielawski]].\n* Musa \u00c7axarxan Czachorowski, Polish Tatar.\n\n===Portuguese===\n* [[Helmi Nasr]], ''Tradu\u00e7\u00e3o do Sentido do Nobre Alcor\u00e3o''. Medina (Ar\u00e1bia Saudita), Complexo de Impress\u00e3o do Rei Fahd, 2005 (1426 A.H.), edi\u00e7\u00e3o bil\u00edng\u00fce (\u00e1rabe/portugu\u00eas).\n* [[Samir El Hayek]], ''O Significado dos Vers\u00edculos do Alcor\u00e3o Sagrado''. S\u00e3o Paulo, Ed. Marsam, 1994. [1\u00aa ed. 1974].\n* [[Mansour Challita]], ''O Alcor\u00e3o \u2013 Livro Sagrado do Isl\u00e3''. Rio de Janeiro, Ed. Record, 2013.\n* [[Jos\u00e9 Pedro Machado]], ''Alcor\u00e3o''. Lisboa, Junta de Investiga\u00e7\u00f5es Cient\u00edficas do Ultramar 1979.\n* [[Am\u00e9rico de Carvalho]], ''Alcor\u00e3o''. Mem Martins, Publica\u00e7\u00f5es Europa-Am\u00e9rica, 1978.\n* [[M. Yiossuf Mohamed Adamgy]], ''Alcor\u00e3o Sagrado''. Loures, Al Furq\u00e1n, 1991, edi\u00e7\u00e3o bil\u00edng\u00fce (\u00e1rabe/portugu\u00eas).\n* [[Bento de Castro]], ''Alcor\u00e3o / Muhamad''. Louren\u00e7o Marques (Mo\u00e7ambique), Oficinas Gr\u00e1ficas de J. A. Carvalho, 1964.\n\n===Romanian===\n* [[Silvestru Octavian Isopescul]], ''Coranul'', 1912 (first edition)\n* Islamic and Cultural League of Romania, ''Traducerea Sensurilor Coranului Cel Sf\u00e2nt \u00een Limba Rom\u00e2n\u0103'', 1997 (first edition)\n* [[George Grigore]], ''Coranul'', 2000 (first edition)\n* Mustafa Ali Mehmed, ''Coran: Ultima Carte Sf\u00e2nt\u0103'', 2003 (first edition)\n\n===Romani===\n* [[Muharem Serbezovski]] is known as a singer in [[North Macedonia]] and [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]] where he issued his translation.<ref>[http://www.rferl.org/content/article/1062583.htmlRomany Koran Published In Bosnia] {{dead link|date=April 2017|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref>\n\n===Russian===\n* P. V. Postnikov.<ref name=\"ReferenceA\"/>\n* M. I. Veryovkin.\n* A. V. Kolmakov.\n* K. Nikolayev.\n* D. N. Boguslavsky.\n* G. S. Sablukov.\n* I. Yu. Krachkovsky.\n* T. A. Shumovsky.\n* Sh. B. Yakovlevna.\n* M.-N. O. Osmanov.\n* V. M. Porokhova.\n* E. R. Kuliev.\n\n=== Sanskrit ===\n\n=== Saraiki ===\nThere are more than twenty translations of Quran in [[Saraiki language|Saraiki]].{{citation needed|date = October 2016}} <!--Dr. Maqbool Hassan Gillani did his Doctrate in Saraiki Translations of Quran.-->\n* Hafizur Rahman, in the 1930s<ref>{{Cite journal |last=Shackle |first=Christopher| author-link = Christopher Shackle |title=Siraiki: A Language Movement in Pakistan |journal=Modern Asian Studies |issn=0026-749X |volume=11 |issue=3 |pages=379\u2013403 |date=1977 |jstor=311504 |doi=10.1017/s0026749x00014190}}</ref>{{rp|391}}\n* Dr. Meher Abdul Haq.\n*[[:ur:\u062f\u0644\u0634\u0627\u062f_\u06a9\u0644\u0627\u0646\u0686\u0648\u06cc|Prof. Dilshad Klanchvi]], in the 2000. Published by [[:ur:\u0627\u0628\u0646_\u06a9\u0644\u06cc\u0645|Ibn-e-Kaleem]] titled as [https://www.scribd.com/document/377489119/Complete-Quran-Arabic-with-Saraiki-Translation \"SAUKH-E-SARAIKI TARJAMAY WALA QURAN SHAREEF\"]\n* Riaz Shahid.\n* Dr. Sadeeque Shakir.\n* G. R. Sevra.\n* Dr. Tahir Khakwani, complete video translation in Saraiki.\n\n===Serbian===\n* [[Mi\u0107o Ljubibrati\u0107]]: Koran. Translated from Russian or French. Beograd, 1895, Sarajevo, 1990 (reprint), 2016.\n\n===Sindhi===\n* According to Sindhi tradition the first translation was made by in 270/883 by an [[Arabs|Arab]] scholar. This one might be the same as the one mentioned above. The first extant [[Sindhi language|Sindhi]] translation was done by [[Akhund Azaz Allah Muttalawi]] (1160-1240/1747-1824) and first published in [[Gujarat]] in 1870. The first to appear in print was by Muhammad Siddiq (Lahore 1867).<ref>[http://www.imamreza.net/eng/imamreza.php?id=1391 The Holy Qur'an and its Translators] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160115045637/http://www.imamreza.net/eng/imamreza.php?id=1391 |date=15 January 2016 }}</ref>\n* First ever translation of Quran to any other language was in [[Sindhi language]] by [[Imam Abul Hassan bin Mohammad Sadiq Al-Sindhi Al-Madni]].\n* [[Maulana Abdul Waheed Jan Sirhindi]], a contemporary scholar and writer of [[Sunni Islam]].<ref>[http://sirhindi.info/books.html Translation of Quran in Sindhi by Maulana Abdul Waheed Jan Sirhindi] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141012003115/http://sirhindi.info/books.html |date=12 October 2014 }}</ref>\n* [[Allama Ali Khan Abro]], wrote Sindhi translation of [[Quran]] and intended to give the Qur'an a practical contemporary interpretation also wrote separate translation for non-Muslims from the request of Sindh's great freedom fighter [[Maulana Taj Mohammad Amrothi]].\n* [[Allama Makhdoom Muhammad Hashim Thattvi]]\n* Maulana Ghullam Mustafa Qasmi's Sindhi Translation of the Quran.\n* [[Maulvi Ahmad Mallah]]'s poetic Sindhi Translation of the Quran.\n* [[Maulana Abdul Karim Qureshi of Bair Shareef]] District [[Qamber Shahdadkot District|Kambar Shahdadkot]]- Sindhi Translation of the Quran.\n* [[Maulana Taj Mohammad Amrothi|Maulana Taj Mohammad Amroti]]'s Sindhi Translation of the Quran.\n* Amir Bakhsh Channa's Sindhi Translation of the Quran.\n* [[Mufti Muhammad Raheem Sikandri]] resident of [[Pir jo Goth]] Dargah Shareef Pagara [[Sindh]],\n* [Molana Abdul Salam soomro Advocate (khanpur District shikarpur) Sindhi Translation of the Quran word by word in fist time, published by sindhica Academy, Karachi, in year 2017. and second publication was made in 2018 with translation of molana taj mohammad Amroti, [[Pakistan]]\n\n=== Sinhala ===\n\n===[[Spanish language|Spanish]]===\n* Anonymous ''morisco'''s translation, made in 1606,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://archive.org/details/coran-aljamiado |title=Cor\u00e1n aljamiado |first=570-632 |last=Mahoma |date=6 March 2018 |publisher= |via=Internet Archive}}</ref> published in 2001 by Reial Acad\u00e8mia de Bones Lletres de Barcelona.\n* Julio Cortes translation ''El Coran'' is widely available in North America, being published by New York-based ''Tahrike Tarsile Qur'an'' publishing house.\n* Ahmed Abboud and Rafael Castellanos, two converts to Islam of Argentine origin, published ''El Sagrado Coran'' (El Nilo, Buenos Aires, Argentina, 1953).\n* Kamal Mustafa Hallak fine deluxe Hardback print ''El Coran Sagrado'' is printed by Maryland-based Amana Publications.\n* Abdel Ghani Melara Navio a Spaniard who converted to Islam in 1979, his ''Traduccion-Comentario Del Noble Coran'' was originally published by Darussalam Publications, Riyadh, in December 1997. The King Fahd Printing Complex has their own version of this translation, with editing by Omar Kaddoura and Isa Amer Quevedo.\n* \"El Sagrado Cor\u00e1n\", translated by Antonio Carrillo Robles and published in 1988 by the [[Ahmadiyya]] Muslim Community (considered heretic by orthodox Muslims) in C\u00f3rdoba, Spain.\n\n===[[Sundanese language|Sundanese]]===\n* ''Tafsir Al-Foerqan Basa Sunda'' by A. Hassan, 1937.\n* ''Nurul-Bajan: Tafsir Qur\u2019an Basa Sunda'' by H. Mhd. Romli and H.N.S. Midjaja, 1960.\n* ''Al-Amin: Al-Qur\u2019an Tarjamah Sunda'' by K.H. Qamaruddin Shaleh, H.A.A. Dahlan, and Yus Rusamsi, 1971.\n* Translation and commentary by K.H. Anwar Musaddad, K.H. Mhd. Romli, K.H. Hambali Ahmad, K.H.I. Zainuddin, K. Moh. Salmon et al., 1978.\n* ''Tafsir Ayat Suci Lenyepaneun'' by Moh. E. Hasim, 1984.\n* ''Nur Hidayah: Saritilawah Basa Sunda'' in Sundanese poem by H.R. Hidayat Surayalaga, 1994.\n* ''Al-Munir: Al-Qur\u2019an Tarjamah Basa Sunda'' by H.M. Djawad Dahlan, 2005.<ref>[http://sundaislam.wordpress.com/2008/01/09/alquran-dan-tafsir-sunda/ Alquran dan Tafsir Sunda] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160315191021/http://sundaislam.wordpress.com/2008/01/09/alquran-dan-tafsir-sunda/ |date=15 March 2016 }}</ref>\n\n===Swahili===\nAt least 7 complete translations in Swahili have appeared and dozens of partial translations.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://etheses.bham.ac.uk/150/1/Chesworth08PhD.pdf |title=Archived copy |accessdate=24 December 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130102173947/http://etheses.bham.ac.uk/150/1/Chesworth08PhD.pdf |archivedate=2 January 2013 }}</ref>\n* [[Tafsiri ya Kurani ya Kiarabu kwa lugha ya Kiswahili pamoja na Dibaji na maelezo Machache]] by [[Godfrey Dale]], 1923\n* [[Kurani Tukufu]] by [[Mubarak Ahmad Ahmadi]], 1953\n* [[Qur' ani Takatifu]] by [[Abdallah Saleh al-Farsy]], 1969\n* [[Tarjama ya al-muntakhab katika tafsiri ya Qur' ani tukufu]] by [[Ali Muhsin Al-Barwani]], 1995\n* [[Kitabu kinachobainisha]] by [[Ali Juma Mayunga]], 2003\n* [[Asili ya Uongofu]] by Said Moosa al-Kindy, 1992\u20132013 (final volume expected 2014)\n* [[Al-Kashif]] by [[Muhammad Jawad Mughniyya]] translated in Swahili by Hasan Mwalupa<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.al-islam.org/sw/al-kashif-juzuu-ya-kwanza/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=24 December 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160529130124/http://www.al-islam.org/sw/al-kashif-juzuu-ya-kwanza |archivedate=29 May 2016 }}</ref>\n\n===Swedish===\n* Carl Johan Tornberg, 1875.<ref>[[:sv:Carl Johan Tornberg]]</ref>\n* [[Karl Vilhelm Zetterst\u00e9en]], 1917.<ref>[http://www.fomi.nu/files/islam_koranen.php Evaluation of Zetterst\u00e9ens translation (in Swedish)] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070928084252/http://www.fomi.nu/files/islam_koranen.php |date=28 September 2007 }}</ref>\n* [[Mohammed Knut Bernstr\u00f6m]]\n\n===[[Tamil language|Tamil]]===\n* Iqbal Madani\n* A.K. Abdhul Hameed Bakavi, 1929, [[Madras]]\n* K.A. Nizamudeen Manbavee\n* Moulavi P. Jainulabdeen Ulavi\n* MOHAMED RIFASH.O\n\n===Tatar===\n* [[Musa Bigiev]]\n\n===Telugu===\n* Divya Quran Sandesham<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.telugu-quran.com/en/index.html |title=Telugu Quran|website=www.telugu-quran.com}}</ref> by Dr. Abdul-Raheem Mohammed Moulana\n*Divya Quran by [http://thechoice.one/noble-quran-telugu-\u0c24\u0c46\u0c32\u0c41\u0c17\u0c41-translation-audio-mp3/ JANAB HAMIDULLAH SHARIEF SAHEB] first translator of Telugu Quran\n*BHAVAMRUTAM by JANAB [http://www.islamic-resource-centre.org/irc-publication.html ABUL IRFAN] SAHEB\n*Quran AVAGAHANAM by JANAB S M MALLICK SAHEB. This is translation of [[Tafhim-ul-Quran|TAFHEEMUL]] QURAN by MAULANA [[Abul A'la Maududi|SAYYED ABUL ALA MAUDOODI]]\n*\n\n===Thai===\n*King Fahad Quran Complex [http://tanzil.net/#trans/th.thai/19:1]\n* Abu Israfil al-Fatani, 2009 [http://archive.org/details/thaiquranabuisrafil20190721]\n\n===Turkish===\nOver fifty translations of the Koran have appeared in Turkish.<ref>[http://www.quran.org.uk/articles/ieb_quran_translators.htm ] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080516042333/http://www.quran.org.uk/articles/ieb_quran_translators.htm |date=16 May 2008 }}</ref> Although it has been claimed that the Koran was first translated into Turkish on the instructions of Kemal Atat\u00fcrk,<ref>[http://www.silkroadstudies.org/new/inside/turkey/2008/080521-TRA.pdf The Turkey Analyst, 21-05-2008] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130708112546/http://www.silkroadstudies.org/new/inside/turkey/2008/080521-TRA.pdf |date=8 July 2013 }}</ref> other sources claim that Turkish translations have existed since the beginning of the Muslim era<ref>[http://www.ha.shotoku.ac.jp/library/HP-bak/kiyo/gaikoku/gaikoku44/volker.pdf On Translating the Holy Qu\u2019ran, Craig Alan Volker] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120309212735/http://www.ha.shotoku.ac.jp/library/HP-bak/kiyo/gaikoku/gaikoku44/volker.pdf |date=9 March 2012 }}</ref>\n* Sheikh Al-Fadl Mohamed Ben Idriss.\n* ''Tafsir al-Tibyiin'', 1842, Cairo.\n* Ahmad b. 'Abd Allah, 1875, ''Tafsir-e zubdat al-athar'', 2 vol. Istanbul 1292-1294/1875-77, p.&nbsp;448+464.\n* Ibrahim Hilmi, 1913 ''Terjumat el Koran'', Istanbul\n* [[Elmal\u0131l\u0131 Muhammed Hamdi Yaz\u0131r]], 1935, ''[[Elmal\u0131l\u0131 Muhammed Hamdi Yaz\u0131r#Works|Hakk D\u012bni Kur'an Dili]] [[Quran translations|yeni]] [[Quran translations#Turkish|mealli]] [[Turkish language|T\u00fcrk\u00e7e]] [[tafsir]]'', 9 vol. Istanbul 1935\u20131938\\ 9 vol. 2nd ed. Istanbul 1960\u20131962, p.&nbsp;6632+229\\ 9 vol. 3rd ed. Istanbul 1970, p.&nbsp;6432+229.\n* \u00d6mer R\u0131za Do\u011frul, 1943-1955/1980, ''Tanr\u0131 Buyru\u011fu: Kur\u2019\u00e2n-\u0131 Ker\u00eem\u2019in Terc\u00fcme ve Tefsiri'', \u0130stanbul 1943, 1947, 1955, 1980\n* ''Syed Mahmood Tarazi Al Madani Bin Syed Nazir Trazi (D:1991) '' translated Qur'an in Turkistani (Chag'atay Uzbek ) in 1956, (First Published: 1956 Bombay )\n*[[Abd\u00fclbaki G\u00f6lp\u0131narl\u0131|Abd\u00fclb\u00e2ki G\u00f6lp\u0131narl\u0131]], 1955, Istanbul 1968, p.&nbsp;688\\ 2 vol. Istanbul 1955, p. (38l)+(381 +Cxxxviii)\n* Huseyin Atay and Yasar Kutluay, 1961, 3 vol. Ankara 1961, p.&nbsp;32+814+7\\ 1 vol. 5th ed. Ankara: Diyanet isleri Baskanligi (The Turkish Presidency of Religious Affairs), 1980, p.&nbsp;34+604\n* [[S\u00fcleyman Ate\u015f]], 1975, 1st ed. Istanbul 1975. p.&nbsp;592\\ Ankara: KilicKitabevi 1977, p.&nbsp;2+604+3+xxx\n* Ali Bula\u00e7, 1985, Istanbul: Birim 1985, p. xxxviii+605.\n* [[Ya\u015far Nuri \u00d6zt\u00fcrk]], 1993.\n* [[Edip Y\u00fcksel]], 2000, ''Mesaj Kuran \u00c7evirisi'', ({{ISBN|975-7891-31-2}}).\n* [[Ahmed Hulusi]], 2009, All\u00e2h \u0130lminden Yans\u0131malarla KUR'\u00c2N-I KER\u00ceM \u00c7\u00d6Z\u00dcM\u00dc (The Key to the Quran)<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ahmedhulusi.org/kuran/ |title=Kuran - ahmedhulusi.org |website=ahmedhulusi.org}}</ref>\n* Hakk\u0131 Y\u0131lmaz, 2012, N\u00dcZUL SIRASINA G\u00d6RE NECM NECM KUR'AN MEAL\u0130 <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.istekuran.net |title= Hakk\u0131 Y\u0131lmaz - \u0130\u015fte Kuran |website=www.istekuran.net}}</ref>\n\n===Tajik===\n*AbdolMohammad Ayati [http://tanzil.net/#trans/tg.ayati/19:1]\n\n===Ukrainian===\n* [[Mykhaylo Yakubovych]], \"Preslavnyj Koran: pereklad smysliv Ukrajns'koju movoju\", 2012.\n\n===[[Urdu language|Urdu]]===\n*''Anwaar-Al-Quran'' by [[Allama Syed Zeeshan Haider Jawadi]] (R.A). First edition published in 1990 by Tanzeem-Al-Makatib, Golaganj, Lucknow, Uttar Pradesh, India.\n*[[Kanzul Iman]] by [[Ahmad Raza Khan|Ala Hazrat Imam Ahmad Raza Khan]] [[Barelvi|Barelvi Alaihirrahama]].<ref name=\"SkresletSkreslet2006\"/><ref name=\"Available in archive\">url={{cite web |url=https://archive.org/details/HolyQurankanzulImaanWithTransla