h company, 2011.\n* \"Mutalaeh Quran \u0645\u0637\u0627\u0644\u0639\u06c1 \u0642\u0631\u0622\u0646\" by ABDULLAH, 2014, can be downloaded in pdf form from google.<ref name=\"google.com\"/><ref>{{cite web |url=https://sites.google.com/site/myquranpak |title=Archived copy |accessdate=30 January 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160917034813/https://sites.google.com/site/myquranpak/ |archivedate=17 September 2016 }}</ref>\n\nFollowing translations are known to exist, but need more information, such as publisher, title, year of publication etc.\n* Maulana Aashiq Ilahi Meeruti, ''Tarjama Quran''.\n* Translation By Majils-e-Fikr o Nazar-Matalib-ul-Quraan.\n* Mualana Hakeem Yaseen Shah.\n* Mufti Imdadullah Anwar.\n* Dr. Muhammad Din Peshaweri Taleem ul Quran a word to word and idiomatic rendering of the Holy Quran. 2000.\n* Maulana Mahmood Hassan.\n* Dr. Abdur-Raoof, Ferozsons Publishers.\n* Maulana Abdul Bari, Hederabadi Daccni, India.\n* Maulana Sufi Abdul Hameed Sawati.\n* Maulana Ishaaq Kashmeri (Dubai) Zubdatul-Quraan.\n* Maulana Abdul Majjid Daryabadi, India.\n* Maulana Aashiq Illahi Merathi, India.\n* Maulana Ahmad Ali Lahori.\n* Dr. Hamid Hasan Bilgarami, Fayuz ul Quraan 2 Vols.\n* Maulana Abdul Kareem Pareekh, India.\n* Maulana Aashiq Illahi Bulandshaheri.\n* Maulana Abu Haq Haqani Dehlvi.\n* Shah Rafi al-Din.\n* Shah 'Abd al-Qadir.\n* Fatheh Mohammad Khan.\n* Maulana Muhammad Ali (India).\n* Maulana Maqbool Ahmed Dhelwi (Known as Maqbool).\n* Allama Azad Subhani (1897\u20131964) wrote ''Tafsir e Rabbani Mukaddama''\n* [[Tahir ul Qadri]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.minhaj.org/english/tid/8718/A-Profile-of-Shaykh-ul-Islam-Dr-Muhammad-Tahir-ul-Qadri.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=15 April 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160803000922/http://www.minhaj.org/english/tid/8718/A-Profile-of-Shaykh-ul-Islam-Dr-Muhammad-Tahir-ul-Qadri.html |archivedate=3 August 2016 }} Tahir-ul-Qadri</ref> ''Irfan-ul-Quran''.<ref>{{cite web |author=Minhaj Internet Bureau |url=http://www.irfan-ul-quran.com |title=English Quran \u2013 Irfan-ul-Quran, Read Listen Search Download & Buy the Comprehensive & Self-Sufficient translation of Holy Quran where general reader does not need any exegesis |publisher=Irfan-ul-quran.com |date= |accessdate=14 May 2013}}</ref>\n\n===Uyghur===\n*Muhammed Saleh. [http://tanzil.net/#trans/ug.saleh/19:1]\n\n===[[Yiddish]]===\n* Selected parts translated in 1987<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.alislam.org/quran/selected-verses/Yiddish.pdf |title=Archived copy |accessdate=17 September 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304060200/http://www.alislam.org/quran/selected-verses/Yiddish.pdf |archivedate=4 March 2016 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Hovel |first=Revital |url=http://www.haaretz.com/jewish-world/jewish-world-news/muslim-sect-celebrates-25-years-since-koran-translated-into-yiddish.premium-1.461072 |title=Muslim sect celebrates 25 years since Koran translated into Yiddish \u2013 Israel News &#124; Haaretz Daily Newspaper |publisher=Haaretz.com |date=28 August 2012 |accessdate=14 May 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://forward.com/articles/162473/the-yiddish-quran/ |title=The Yiddish Quran \u2013 |publisher=Forward.com |date= |accessdate=14 May 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://gbtimes.wordpress.com/2014/04/01/alijah-ghulam-uddin-ghulam-hunzai-an-intelectual-jewel-of-gilgit-baltistan/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=28 September 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304204128/https://gbtimes.wordpress.com/2014/04/01/alijah-ghulam-uddin-ghulam-hunzai-an-intelectual-jewel-of-gilgit-baltistan/ |archivedate=4 March 2016 }}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[English translations]]\n*[[List of Ahmadi translations of the Quran]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Wikisource|The Holy Qur'an}}\n* [http://EnglishQuran.com English Quran Translations Side-by-Side with Arabic Dictionary and Recitations]\n* [http://www.tanzil.net Tanzil]\n* [http://al-quran.info Al-Quran] project includes 140+ translations in more than 30 languages.\n* [https://app.box.com/s/j3b5lmqt8zbbm68e7igk Downloadable Taleem-ul-Quran]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:List Of Translations Of The Qur'an}}\n[[Category:Quran translations|*]]\n[[Category:Quran-related lists|Translations]]\n[[Category:Translation-related lists|Qur'an]]\n[[Category:Quran translations by language]]\n\n[[ms:Penterjemahan Al-Quran]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2019}}\n{{Quran|all}}\n{{Translation sidebar}}\n:''This is a sub-article to [[Qur'an translations]].''\n\n==Historical (up to the 21st century)==\n\n===7th\u201310th centuries===\n* [[Salman the Persian]] translated the first chapter of the Qur'an, [[Al-Fatiha]], from Arabic to [[Persian language|Persian]].<ref>An-Nawawi, Al-Majmu', (Cairo, Matbacat at-'Tadamun n.d.), 380.</ref>\n* [[Greek language|Greek]]: The purpose is unknown but it is confirmed to be the first ever complete translation of the Quran. We know of it (and substantial fragments are preserved) because it was used by [[Nicetas Byzantius]], a scholar from [[Constantinople]], in his 'Refutatio' written between 855 and 870.<ref>Christian H\u00f8gel, \"An early anonymous Greek translation of the Qur'an. The fragments from Niketas Byzantios' Refutatio and the anonymous Abjuratio\", ''Collectanea Christiana Orientalia'' 7 (2010), pp. 65\u2013119; [[Kees Versteegh]], \"Greek translations of the Quran in Christian polemics (9th century)\", ''Zeitschrift der Deutschen morgenl\u00e4ndischen Gesellschaft'' 141 (1991); Ast\u00e9rios Argyriou, \"Perception de l'Islam et traductions du Coran dans le monde byzantin grec\", ''Byzantion'' 75 (2005); Christian H\u00f8gel, The Greek Qur'an: scholarship and evaluations. Orientalia Suecana, 61 (Suppl.) (2013), pp. 173\u2013180.</ref>\n*Although not existing today, a [[Sindhi language|Sindhi]] translation was completed in 994 in Alwar (present-day [[Sindh]], [[Pakistan]]), which had been commissioned by Abdullah bin Umar bin Abdul Aziz.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.monthlycrescent.com/understanding-the-quran/english-translations-of-the-quran/ |title=English Translations of the Quran \" Crescent |publisher=Monthlycrescent.com |accessdate=14 May 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140429213509/http://www.monthlycrescent.com/understanding-the-quran/english-translations-of-the-quran/ |archive-date=29 April 2014 |url-status=dead  }}</ref>\nThis is inferred from two references:\n\"\u2026 an anonymous early 9th century Kashmiri Hindu king ...\" wrote a letter to Amir Abdullah bin Umar bin Abdul Aziz of Mansura, requesting him to dispatch a scholar to his court who could explain the tenets of the Islamic shariah in the language \"al-Hindia\".<ref>Directorate of Information, Kashmir Today, Srinagar: Government of  Jammu and Kashmir, 1998, pp. 113\u201314.</ref>\nThe 9th century Persian traveller Buzurg bin Shahryar mentions in his travelogue, Aja\u0092ib-ul Hind [\u0091The Wonders of India\u0092], that the Hindu king of Mehroke in Kashmir had commissioned the preparation of a Kashmiri translation of the Quran.<ref>Khwaja Muhammad 'Azam Didamari, Waqi'at-i-Kashmir (The History of Kashmir) [translated by Khwaja Hamid Yazdani], Srinagar: Jammu and Kashmir Islamic Research Center, 1998, p. 117.</ref>\n\n*An incomplete [[Berber languages|Berber]] translation may have been promulgated by the [[Barghawata]] King [[Salih ibn Tarif]] in the 8th century, radically expanded with original, non-Quranic material which he claimed had been [[Revelation|revealed]] [[Prophet|to him]].\n\n===10th century===\n*''Tafsir-e Tabari'': The first complete translation of the Quran in [[Persian literature|Persian]], along with its [[tafsir]], which has survived till today. The book is a translation of [[Tafsir al-Tabari]] in Arabic.\n\n===11th century===\n* Persian translation which is called \"Qur'an Quds\" which was translated by an unknown translator.<ref>{{cite web |title=Qur'an Quds |url=http://www.al-shia.com/html/far/books/quran&olum/quran_paju/q_pagh04.htm |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110830093923/http://www.al-shia.com/html/far/books/quran%26olum/quran_paju/q_pagh04.htm |archivedate=30 August 2011 }}</ref>\n*''Kashf al-Israr wa 'Eddat al-Abrar'': Complete translation and tafsir of Quran in Persian by one of the students of [[Khwaja Abdullah Ansari|Abu Mansur Abdullah al-Ansari]]. The book is available and has been published.\n\n===12th century===\n*1143, [[Latin]], ''[[Lex Mahumet pseudoprophete]]'', by a group led by [[Robert of Ketton]], under direction of [[Peter the Venerable]]\n*''Tafsir Nasafi'': Complete Persian translation, along with the Quran exegesis, by [[Abu Hafs Omar al-Nasafi|Najm al-Din Abu Hafs al-Nasafi]]. The work has recently been published.\n\n===13th century===\n*1193\u20131216, [[Latin]], an improved Latin translation from Arabic by [[Mark of Toledo]] ([[floruit|fl.]] 1193\u20131216)\n\n===16th century===\n*1543 reprint Latin text of ''Lex Mahumet pseudoprophete'' (1143), edited by [[Theodor Bibliander]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Qur'an translation by T. Bibliander, etc. from msgr.ca |url=http://www.msgr.ca/msgr-2/Koran%20-%20Nativity%20-%2001.htm |access-date=12 May 2006 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081228105904/http://www.msgr.ca/msgr-2/Koran%20-%20Nativity%20-%2001.htm |archive-date=28 December 2008 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n*1547 enigmatical Italian edition, printed at [[Venice]]\n*Belarusian Tatars` manuscripts ([[kitabs]])<ref>{{cite web |title=Kitabs, the unique highlight of the Belarusian language |url=http://www.pravapis.org/art_kitab1_en.asp |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20020830171327/http://www.pravapis.org/art_kitab1_en.asp |url-status=dead |archive-date=30 August 2002 }}</ref>\n\n===17th century===\n* 17th century [[Malay language|Malay]], ''Tafsir Tarjuman al-Mustafid'' by Shaikh Abdur Ra'uf al-Fansuri from [[Aceh Sultanate]]. This is the first translation in [[Malay language]]. The translation is in the classical Malay language (not to be confused with [[Malaysian language]]) before it evolved into the [[Indonesian language]] and the [[Malaysian language]] in recent times. This translation was written with [[Jawi alphabet|Jawi script]].<ref name=\"ulama-nusantara.blogspot.com\">[http://ulama-nusantara.blogspot.com/2007/09/syeikh-abdur-rauf-fansuri-pentafsir-al.html Syeikh Abdur Rauf Fansuri pentafsir al-Quran pertama dalam bahasa Melayu] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303225134/http://ulama-nusantara.blogspot.com/2007/09/syeikh-abdur-rauf-fansuri-pentafsir-al.html |date=3 March 2016 }}</ref><ref name=\"Tarjuman al-Mustafid\">[http://wahyunishifaturrahmah.wordpress.com/2010/02/16/mempertimbangkan-tarjuman-al-mustafid-telaah-atas-kemurnian-tafsir-karya-abd-rauf-sinkel/ Tarjuman al-Mustafid] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305232533/http://wahyunishifaturrahmah.wordpress.com/2010/02/16/mempertimbangkan-tarjuman-al-mustafid-telaah-atas-kemurnian-tafsir-karya-abd-rauf-sinkel/ |date=5 March 2016 }}</ref>\n*1616, German, ''Alcoranus Mahometicus'' from Italian by [[Salomon Schweigger]], Nuremberg.\n*1632, Latin, ''Turcarum Alcoranus'' from Arabic by Johann Zechendorff (1580-1662), unpublished manuscript<ref>Roberto Tottoli: The Latin Translation of the Qur\u02be\u0101n by Johann Zechendorff (1580-1662) discovered in Cairo D\u0101r al-Kutub.  Oriente Moderno, 95.2015, S. 5\u201331</ref>\n*1647, French, ''[[L'Alcoran de Mahomet]]'' from Arabic by [[Andre du Ryer]], the third from the original Arabic directly into a European language, the first two being to Latin (12th century, 13th century).\n*1649, English, ''Alcoran of Mahomet'' from the French by [[Alexander Ross (writer)|Alexander Ross]].\n*1657, [[Dutch language|Dutch]], ''Mahomets Alkoran'' translated from the French by [[Jan Hendriksz Glazemaker]].\n*1686, [[Polish language|Polish]], the \u201c[https://pl.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tefsir_mi\u0144ski Minsk tafsir]\u201d, first suras were written in Turkish, but from the 19th and onwards they were written in Polish language using Arabic alphabet, translation by Tatars.\n*1698, [[Latin]], a third Latin translation from Arabic, extensively annotated, sometimes from a Christian perspective, preceded by a biography of the Prophet and a discussion of Islamic doctrines, by Father [[Louis Maracci]], Padua.<ref name=msgrpage2>{{cite web |title=Qur'an translation by T. Bibliander, etc. from msgr.ca |url=http://www.msgr.ca/msgr-2/Koran%20-%20Nativity%20-%2002.htm |access-date=12 May 2006 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080112001936/http://www.msgr.ca/msgr-2/Koran%20-%20Nativity%20-%2002.htm |archive-date=12 January 2008 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n===18th century===\n*1716, Russian, \u00ab\u0410\u043b\u043a\u043e\u0440\u0430\u043d \u043e \u041c\u0430\u0433\u043e\u043c\u0435\u0442\u0435, \u0438\u043b\u0438 \u0417\u0430\u043a\u043e\u043d \u0442\u0443\u0440\u0435\u0446\u043a\u0438\u0439\u00bb (Al-Koran of Mahomet, or the Turkish Law) by P. V. Postnikov.<ref name=\"ReferenceA\">\u041f. \u0412. \u0413\u0443\u0441\u0442\u0435\u0440\u0438\u043d. \u041f\u0435\u0440\u0432\u044b\u0439 \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0435\u0432\u043e\u0434\u0447\u0438\u043a \u0438 \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0432\u043e\u0435 \u0438\u0437\u0434\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u041a\u043e\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0430 \u043d\u0430 \u0440\u0443\u0441\u0441\u043a\u043e\u043c \u044f\u0437\u044b\u043a\u0435 // \u0418\u0441\u043b\u0430\u043c\u043e\u0432\u0435\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435. \u2014 2011. \u2014 \u2116 1.</ref>\n*1734, English, ''The Koran'' by [[George Sale]], Translated into English immediately from the original Arabic with explanatory notes and commentaries and evidently making use of the Latin translation of Maracci (1698).<ref>One of the copies owned by American Founding Father [[Thomas Jefferson]], on which [[Keith Ellison (politician)|Keith Ellison]], the first [[Muslim]] elected to [[110th Congress|Congress]], was sworn.</ref>\n*1749, [[Sindh]], \"Tafsir-e-Hashmi\" by [[Makhdoom Muhammad Hashim Thattvi]]. First commentary of the Quran in [[Sindhi language|Sindhi]] and the most ancient translation of [[Quran]] in [[Sindhi language|Sindhi]] that could be found. Popularly called as the first Sindhi translation that got to be known also.\n*1790, Russian, \"\u041a\u043d\u0438\u0433\u0430 \u0410\u043b\u044c-\u041a\u043e\u0440\u0430\u043d \u0430\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043b\u044f\u043d\u0438\u043d\u0430 \u041c\u0430\u0433\u043e\u043c\u0435\u0442\u0430 \u2026\" by M. I. Veryovkin.\n*1792, Russian, \"\u0410\u043b-\u041a\u043e\u0440\u0430\u043d \u041c\u0430\u0433\u043e\u043c\u0435\u0434\u043e\u0432 \u2026\" by A. V. Kolmakov.\n\n===19th century===\n*1834, [[Gustav Leberecht Fl\u00fcgel]]'s text formed the foundation of modern Qur'an research and the basis for several new translations into European languages.<ref>{{cite web |title=Information about Qur'an's translations from website idc.nl in pdf format |url=http://www.idc.nl/pdf/dissemination_quran.pdf}}</ref>\n*1858, Polish, ''Quran (al Quran)'' by Jan Murza Tarak Buczacki.\n*1861, English, ''The Koran'' by [[John Medows Rodwell]].<ref name=msgrpage2/>\n*1864, Russian, \"\u041a\u043e\u0440\u0430\u043d \u041c\u0430\u0433\u043e\u043c\u0435\u0434\u0430\" by K. Nikolayev.\n*1871 (issued 1995), Russian, \"\u041a\u043e\u0440\u0430\u043d \u041c\u0430\u0433\u043e\u043c\u0435\u0434\u0430\" by D. N. Boguslavsky.\n*1878 (reissued a lot of times), Russian, \"\u041a\u043e\u0440\u0430\u043d, \u0437\u0430\u043a\u043e\u043d\u043e\u0434\u0430\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0430\u044f \u043a\u043d\u0438\u0433\u0430 \u043c\u043e\u0445\u0430\u043c\u043c\u0435\u0434\u0430\u043d\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0432\u0435\u0440\u043e\u0443\u0447\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f\" by G. S. Sablukov.\n*1880, English, ''The Koran'', by [[Edward Henry Palmer]].\n*1886, [[Bengali language|Bengali]], by [[Girish Chandra Sen]]\n\n===20th century===\n*1912, [[Urdu]], ''[[Kanzul Iman]]'' by [[Ahmed Raza Khan Barelvi|Ala Hazrat Imam Ahmad Raza Khan Qadri, Barkaati, Muhaddith e Bareilly, Bareilly, UP, India]].\nlater translated into various other languages including English.\n*1902, [[Urdu]], ''Tarjamul Quran'' by Maulana Aashiq Ilahi Meeruti.\n*1905, [[Urdu]], ''Bayanul Quran'' by [[Ashraf Ali Thanwi|Maulana Ashraf Ali Thanvi]].\n*1915\u201319, [[Urdu]], ''Tarjama Shaikhul Hind'' by Shaikhul Hind Maulana Deobandi.\n*1930, English, ''[[The Meaning of the Glorious Koran]]'', by [[Marmaduke Pickthall]].({{ISBN|1-879402-51-3}})\n*1934, English, ''[[The Holy Qur'an: Text, Translation and Commentary]]'', by [[Abdullah Yusuf Ali]].({{ISBN|0-915957-76-0}})\n*1936, [[Bosnian Language|Bosnian]], ''Kur'an'' by Hafiz Muhamed Pand\u017ea and [[D\u017eemaludin \u010cau\u0161evi\u0107]]\n*1936, [[Hebrew]], ''AlQur'an'', by Josef Rivlin.\n*1943-1955/1980, Turkish, Tanr\u0131 Buyru\u011fu: Kur\u2019\u00e2n-\u0131 Ker\u00eem\u2019in Terc\u00fcme ve Tefsiri (\u0130stanbul 1943, 1947, 1955, 1980), by \u00d6mer R\u0131za Do\u011frul\n*1955, English, ''[[The Koran Interpreted|The Koran Interpreted: A Translation]]'', by [[Arthur John Arberry]].({{ISBN|0-684-82507-4}})\n*1963 (reissued a lot of times), Russian, \"\u041a\u043e\u0440\u0430\u043d\" by I. Yu. Krachkovsky.\n*1971, English, ''The Quran'', by Muhammad Zafrulla Khan.\n*1971, Hebrew, ''HaQur'an'', by [[Aharon Ben-Shemesh]].\n*1974, English, ''The Message of the Qur'an : Presented in Perspective'' by Dr. [[Hashim Amir Ali]] (Hyderabad, Deccan, India). He translated the Qur'an into English and arranged it according to chronological order.\n*1978, [[Kannada language]], ''Divya Qur'an, Qur'an Majid'', (An effort of six scholars: Mawlana Shah Abd al-Qadir, Mawlana Sayyid, Abu Raihan Ahmed Noori, Abd Allah Sahib, I\u2019jaz al-Din and Abd al-Ghaffar), 2 volumes, Bangalore.\n*1980, English, ''The Message of The Qur'an'' by [[Muhammad Asad]] (born as Leopold Weiss a Polish Jew, converted to Islam in 1926).\n*1981, English, ''Al Qur'aan'', by As Sayyid Imam Isa Al Haadi Al Mahdi, founder of the Ansaaru Allah Community of the West.\n*1985, English, ''[[Noble Quran (Hilali-Khan)|Noble Qur'an]]'', by [[Muhammad Muhsin Khan]].\n*1985, English, ''The Qur'an: First American Version'', by [[T. B. Irving]].\n*1986, Polish ''Koran'' by [[J\u00f3zef Bielawski]].\n*1987, Hungarian ''Kor\u00e1n'' by R\u00f3bert Simon.\n*1989-05, English, ''The Qur'an'', by [[Muhammad Habib Shakir]].\n*1990s, [[Khowar language]] also known as Chitrali Language, spoken in the North West of Pakistan bordering Afghanistan, by ''Qari Syed Bazurg Shah Al-Azhari'' (Sitara Imtiaz).\n*1990, [[Belarusian language]], ''\u0421\u0432\u044f\u0448\u0447\u044d\u043d\u043d\u044b \u041a\u0430\u0440\u0430\u043d. \u0410\u043d\u0442\u0430\u043b\u043e\u0433\u0456\u044f'', by Tomasz Tamaszewicz, Hrodna, Belarus\n*1991, English, ''The Clarion Call of the Eternal Qur-aan'', by Muhammad Khalilur Rahman from Dhaka, Bangladesh.\n*1991, Hindi, ''Quran Sharif: Anuwad awr Vyakhya'' by Jamiat Ulama Hind, New Delhi, India.\n*1993, [[Sindhi language]], ''Kanzul-i-iman'' by Mufti Muhammad Raheem Sikandri Pir jo Goth Dargah Shareef Pir Pagara.\n*1993, English, ''A Simple Translation of The Holy Qur'an'' (with notes on Topics of Science), by [[Mir Aneesuddin|Dr. Mir Aneesuddin]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Translation |url=http://quranicresources.com/Translation.htm |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120331143639/http://quranicresources.com/Translation.htm |archivedate=31 March 2012 }}</ref>\n*1995, Russian, \u00ab\u041a\u043e\u0440\u0430\u043d\u00bb by T. A. Shumovsky.\n*1995, Russian, \u00ab\u041a\u043e\u0440\u0430\u043d\u00bb by M.-N. O. Osmanov.\n*1996, English, El's Holy Qur'an, by ''[[Malachi Z. York]]'' for the Holy Tabernacle Ministries.\n*1997, Russian, \"\u041a\u043e\u0440\u0430\u043d\" by V. M. Porokhova.\n*1998, [[Swedish language]], ''Koranens budskap'', by [[Mohammed Knut Bernstr\u00f6m]]\n*1998, [[Urdu Language]], English Language ''Bayan-ul-Quran'' by [[Israr Ahmed]]\n\n===21st century===\n*2002, Russian, \"\u041a\u043e\u0440\u0430\u043d\" by E. R. Kuliyev.\n*2005 (January), Bengali Language, \"Al-Qur-aa-nul-Hakeem\" '''<code>(\u0986\u09b2\u0995\u09c1\u09b0\u0986-\u09a8\u09c1\u09b2 \u09b9\u09be\u0995\u09c0\u09ae)</code>''' by [[Professor Maulana Hafez Shaikh Ainul Bari Aliavee,]] Published by Sufia Prakashani, Kolkata (INDIA). {{ISBN|978-81-941079-0-3}}\n*2007, Urdu Language, \"Noor e Imaan\" by Moulana Syed Abid Khundmeeri\n*2010, Telugu Language, ''Divya Quran Sandesham ''by Dr. Abdul-Raheem Mohammed Moulana\n*2011, English, \"AL Quran: By Allah\" by [[Muhammad Kamran Khan]].{{ISBN|978-0-359-61611-4}}\n*2013, Bengali Language, \"Tafseerul Quran\" by [[Muhammad Asadullah Al-Ghalib]], Published by Hadeeth Foundation Bangladesh, can be downloaded in pdf from: {{URL| http://www.ahlehadeethbd.org/books.html| ahlehadeethbd.org }}\n*2013, Georgian \"The Quran\" by [[Giorgi Lobzhanidze]].<ref name=\"festiveart.com\">{{cite web |url=http://www.festiveart.com/NewsDetails.aspx?ID=1997 |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20140805133042/http://www.festiveart.com/NewsDetails.aspx?ID=1997 |url-status=dead |title=Art News, Festive Art . com |date=5 August 2014 |archivedate=5 August 2014 |website=archive.is}}</ref>\n*2014, URDU Language, \"MUTALAEH QURAN \u0645\u0637\u0627\u0644\u0639\u06c1 \u0642\u0631\u0622\u0646\" by ABDULLAH can be downloaded in pdf from [[Google]]<ref name=\"google.com\">{{cite web |url=https://sites.google.com/site/myquranpak |title=MY QURAN PAK |website=sites.google.com}}</ref>\n*2014, URDU Language  \"Mukammal Tafseerul Quran\" by  Mufti shaukat Ali Fehmi, Published by Din Dunia Publishing Co. jama masjid Delhi\n*2016, English,\" Selected collections of Holy Quran in English: A companion for Young Muslims to understand the Divine Messages of Prophet Mohammad\" by Syed N Asad, MD {{ISBN|978-1523877645}}\n*2016, English, \"The Quran: A Complete Revelation\" by [[Sam Gerrans]].\n*2016, \"The Holy Quran and its meaning translation in Georgian language\" by {{ill|Emamqoli Batvani|fa|\u0627\u0645\u0627\u0645\u0642\u0644\u06cc \u0628\u0627\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0646\u06cc}}<ref name=\"archive.org\">{{cite web |url=http://www.iribnews.ir/fa/news/1185339/%D8%AA%D8%B1%D8%AC%D9%85%D9%87-%D9%82%D8%B1%D8%A2%D9%86-%D8%A8%D9%87-%D8%B2%D8%A8%D8%A7%D9%86-%DA%AF%D8%B1%D8%AC%DB%8C |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160626051334/http://www.iribnews.ir/fa/news/1185339/%D8%AA%D8%B1%D8%AC%D9%85%D9%87-%D9%82%D8%B1%D8%A2%D9%86-%D8%A8%D9%87-%D8%B2%D8%A8%D8%A7%D9%86-%DA%AF%D8%B1%D8%AC%DB%8C |url-status=dead |archive-date=26 June 2016 |title=\u062a\u0631\u062c\u0645\u0647 \u0642\u0631\u0622\u0646 \u0628\u0647 \u0632\u0628\u0627\u0646 \u06af\u0631\u062c\u06cc |date=26 June 2016 }}</ref>\n2018, Polish, \"Koran\" by Musa \u00c7axarxan Czachorowski, Polish Tatar, {{ISBN|9788365802088}}, <ref>http://mzr.pl/koran-nowy-przeklad/</ref>.\n\n=== Quran in Excel Format ===\n{{advert|section|date=February 2017}}\n* ''In 2013'', Quran translation  in different languages, Word-by-Word and learning with Grammar {All in  Excel (.xlsx) Format}. Roots, words or topic search by links, prepared by Muhammad Arshad Naseem, can be downloaded<ref>{{cite web |url=https://quranexcel.com |title=Quran-excel |website=Quran-excel}}</ref>\n\n==By writer and language==\n\n===[[Acehnese language|Acehnese]]===\n* Translation in [[Acehnese language|Acehnese]] poem,<ref>[http://samanui.wordpress.com/2007/09/25/peluncuran-al-quran-terjemahan-aceh/ Peluncuran Al-Qur'an Terjemahan Aceh] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160313131603/http://samanui.wordpress.com/2007/09/25/peluncuran-al-quran-terjemahan-aceh/ |date=13 March 2016 }}</ref> by Teungku Mahyiddin Yusuf in 1995.<ref>[http://rambideun.blogspot.com/2007/09/p3ki-luncurkan-alquran-terjemahan.html P3KI Luncurkan Alquran Terjemahan Bahasa Aceh] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304095954/http://rambideun.blogspot.com/2007/09/p3ki-luncurkan-alquran-terjemahan.html |date=4 March 2016 }}</ref> The manuscript is written in [[Jawi script]] but later converted into [[Latin script]] in printed version.<ref>[http://bangcut.blogspot.com/2008/09/kembalikan-budaya-dengan-al-quran.html Kembalikan Budaya dengan Al-Qur'an] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140104170721/http://bangcut.blogspot.com/2008/09/kembalikan-budaya-dengan-al-quran.html |date=4 January 2014 }}</ref> (see pdf)\n\n===Afrikaans===\n* ''Die Heilige Qur'\u0101n'', by Imam Muhammad A Baker.  First edition 1961.  The style of Afrikaans dates from the 1940s\u20131960s.  The author deliberately used spelling which mimicks Arabic pronunciation even if those words have been taken up into mainstream Afrikaans with a different spelling or pronunciation.  It is a literal translation, but the text reads like normal, idiomatic Afrikaans, with a few errors.  The word \"surah\" was translated \"hoofstuk\" (meaning \"chapter\").  The book does not contain the Arabic text.\n* A newer Afrikaans translation of the Qur'an was made using the principles of [[Dynamic and formal equivalence|dynamic equivalence]], but that version is not popular among Afrikaans Muslims.\n\n===Albanian===\n* Ilo Mitke Qaf\u00ebzezi, 1921.\n* Feti Mehdiu, 1985.\n* Hasan Efendi Nahi, 1988.\n* H. Sherif Ahmeti, 1988.\n*''Kurani Kerim'', by Muhammad Zakria Khan. First published in UK in 1990. Second revised edition in 2003. Islam International Publications.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.alislam.org/quran/tafseer/?page%3D-53%26region%3DAL |title=Archived copy |accessdate=26 May 2010 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161226083813/http://www.alislam.org/quran/tafseer/?page=-53&region=AL |archivedate=26 December 2016 }}</ref> ({{ISBN|978-1-85372-324-7}}).\n\n===[[Assamese language|Assamese]]===\n* [[Zohurul Hoque]]. Second revised edition published in 2007 by Bina Library. The book has parallel transliteration of Arabic text into Assamese language.\n\n===[[Azerbaijani language|Azerbaijani]]===\n*Mir M\u0259h\u0259mm\u0259d K\u0259rim a\u011fa (1906)<ref name=\"muallim.edu.az\">[http://www.muallim.edu.az/arxiv/2012/39/45.htm \u0130stedad\u0131n Vasim M\u0259mm\u0259d\u0259liyev zirv\u0259si ]{{dead link|date=December 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }} muallim.edu.az, 5 October 2012</ref>\n*[[Mahammad Hasan Movlazadeh Shakavi]] (1908)<ref name=\"muallim.edu.az\"/>\n*[[Vasim Mammadaliyev]] (1971)<ref name=\"muallim.edu.az\"/>\n*[[Ziya Bunyadov]]\n*[[Alikhan Musayev]]\n\n===Balochi===\n* by Moulana Huzoor Bakhsh\n* Mawlana Khair Ali Nadwi\u062c\u0645\u0627\u0644 \u0627\u0644\u0642\u0631\u0622\u0646 by Mawlana Khair Mohammad Nadwi\n* by Shaikh Abdul Gaffar Zamurani\n* Allama Qazi Abdul Samad Sarbazi and Mawlana Khair Mohammad Nadwi\n\n===Belarusian===\n* [[Kitabs]] written in [[Belarusian Arabic alphabet]] during 15th \u2014 19th centuries.\n* Tomasz Tamaszewicz<ref>\u0421\u0412\u042f\u0428\u0427\u042d\u041d\u041d\u042b \u041a\u0410\u0420\u0410\u041d. \u0410\u041d\u0422\u0410\u041b\u041e\u0413\u0406\u042f. \u041f\u0435\u0440\u0430\u043a\u043b\u0430\u0434 \u0422\u043e\u043c\u0430\u0448\u0430 \u0422\u0430\u043c\u0430\u0448\u044d\u0432\u0456\u0447\u0430. \u0414\u0440\u0443\u043a\u0430\u0432\u0430\u043d\u043d\u0435 \u0434\u0430\u0437\u0432\u043e\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0430 \u041c\u0443\u0444\u0446\u0456\u044f\u0442\u0430\u043c \u0415\u045e\u0440\u0430\u043f\u0435\u0439\u0441\u043a\u0430\u0439 \u0447\u0430\u0441\u0442\u043a\u0456 \u0421\u0421\u0421\u0420 \u0456 \u0421\u0456\u0431\u0456\u0440\u044b \u2014 1990, \u0413\u0440\u043e\u0434\u043d\u0430</ref>\n\n===Bengali===\n* Maulana [[Maulana Muhiuddin Khan|Muhiuddin Khan]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Maulana Mohiuddin Khan passes away |url=http://www.daily-sun.com/printversion/details/147163/Maulana-Mohiuddin-Khan-passes-away |accessdate=1 July 2016 |agency=The Daily Sun |publisher=The Daily Sun}}</ref>\n* Abbas Ali (West Bengal).\n* Mustafizur Rahman.\n* Nurur Rahman, 1984, (Bengali translation of the work by Ashraf Ali Thanvi).\n* 2005 (January), Bengali Language, \"Al-Qur-aa-nul-Hakeem\" '''<code>(\u0986\u09b2\u0995\u09c1\u09b0\u0986-\u09a8\u09c1\u09b2 \u09b9\u09be\u0995\u09c0\u09ae)</code>''' by [[Professor Maulana Hafez Shaikh Ainul Bari Aliavee,]] Published by Sufia Prakashani, Kolkata (INDIA). [[International Standard Book Number|ISBN]] [[Special:BookSources/978-81-941079-0-3|978-81-941079-0-3]]\n*Rafiqur Rahman Chowdhury, 2011, (Bengali translation of the English translation of Quran by [[Abdullah Yusuf Ali]]).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ahsanpublication.com/index.php?main_page%3Dproduct_book_info%26cPath%3D65_69%26products_id%3D524 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=3 February 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305004752/http://ahsanpublication.com/index.php?cpath=65_69&main_page=product_book_info&products_id=524 |archivedate=5 March 2016 }}</ref>\n* Justice Habibur Rahman{{citation needed|date=July 2016}}\n* 2013: [[Muhammad Asadullah Al-Ghalib]],\"Tafseerul Quran\" Published by Hadeeth Foundation Bangladesh, can be downloaded in pdf from: {{URL| http://www.ahlehadeethbd.org/books.html| ahlehadeethbd.org }}\n* Dr Z\u014dhurul Hoque {{citation needed|date=July 2016}}\n* Muhammad Mujibur Rahman. Published bt Darus Salam.{{citation needed|date=July 2016}}\n* Dr Abubakar Muhammad Zakaria\n\n===[[Bosnian language|Bosnian]]===\n* [[D\u017eemaludin \u010cau\u0161evi\u0107]] and [[Muhamed Pand\u017ea]]: Kur'an. Translated from Turkish (\u00d6mer R\u0131za Do\u011frul). Sarajevo, 1937, Zagreb (editors: [[Omer Mu\u0161i\u0107]] and [[Alija Nametak]]), 1969, 1972, 1978, 1984, 1985, 1989, 1990, Dubai, 1993, Sarajevo, 2011, 2012, 2014.\n* [[Ali Riza Karabeg]]: Kur'an. A compilation of the Serbian 