/lesmondeshumanistes/category/dialogue-chretiens-islam/ Bibliander's Qu'ran online] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110621061209/http://sites.univ-lyon2.fr/lesmondeshumanistes/category/dialogue-chretiens-islam/ |date=21 June 2011 }}</ref>\n* Third translation from Arabic 1691\u20131698, by [[Ludovico Marracci]] (Padua).<ref>These volumes remain available to scholars; some claim \"it was in Spanish and not Arab\". {{cite web |url=http://www.destee.com/forums/archive/index.php/t-36212.html |title=According to... |accessdate=18 January 2007 |last=York |first=Malachi |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071008013425/http://www.destee.com/forums/archive/index.php/t-36212.html |archive-date=8 October 2007 |url-status=dead  }}</ref>\n\n===Macedonian===\n* Hasan D\u017eilo, 1997, ''\u041a\u0443\u0440\u02bc\u0430\u043d \u0441\u043e \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0432\u043e\u0434'' (\"the Qur\u02bcan with a Translation\"), [[King Fahd Complex for the Printing of the Holy Quran]] ([[Medina]], [[Saudi Arabia]]).\n* Elena Tren\u010devska\u2013\u010cekovi\u1e31, Mersiha Smailovi\u1e31, Jasmin Red\u017eepi, 2011, ''\u041f\u0440\u0435\u0432\u043e\u0434 \u043d\u0430 \u0437\u043d\u0430\u0447\u0435\u045a\u0435\u0442\u043e \u043d\u0430 \u0411\u043b\u0430\u0433\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0434\u043d\u0438\u043e\u0442 \u041a\u0443\u0440\u0430\u043d'' (\"Translation of the meaning of the Noble Qur\u02bcan\"), ArtBooks ([[Skopje]], [[North Macedonia]]) ({{ISBN|978-9989-190-49-0}}).\n\n===Madura===\n* Translation by Jamaah Pengajian Surabaya (JPS) led by K.H. Sattar.<ref>[http://nu.or.id/page/id/dinamic_detil/1/16433/Warta/Tashih_Al_Qur_an_Madura_Molor.html Tashih Al-Qur'an Madura Molor] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160308102808/http://nu.or.id/page/id/dinamic_detil/1/16433/Warta/Tashih_Al_Qur_an_Madura_Molor.html |date=8 March 2016 }}</ref>\n\n===[[Malayalam]]===\n* Cheriyamundam Abdul Hameed Madani and Kunhi Mohammed Parappoor with online links.<ref>{{cite web |url=ht